# BuildBeaver — Project Structure

## Architecture Overview

BuildBeaver follows **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** for the Next.js frontend, with a completely separate Node.js scraper tool.

```
buildBeaver/
├── src/                        # Next.js app (App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind)
│   ├── app/                    # Route pages and root layout only
│   │   ├── layout.tsx          # Root layout — providers, fonts, metadata
│   │   ├── globals.css         # Global Tailwind base styles
│   │   ├── page.tsx            # Landing / home page
│   │   ├── intake/page.tsx     # Intake form (collects businessType, location, name)
│   │   ├── roadmap/page.tsx    # Roadmap list — renders all STEP_CONFIGS
│   │   └── step/[id]/page.tsx  # Dynamic step detail page
│   ├── entities/               # Domain models and context providers
│   │   └── intake/model/       # IntakeProvider + useIntake hook
│   ├── features/               # Self-contained feature slices (UI + logic together)
│   │   └── form-assistant/ui/  # FormAssistant component (draft & copy form output)
│   └── shared/                 # Pure cross-cutting code — no UI, no side-effects
│       ├── constants/steps.ts  # STEP_CONFIGS array + getStepById()
│       └── types/business.ts   # IntakeData, StepConfig, StepType, OwnershipType
│
├── scraper/                    # Standalone Node.js tool — NOT part of the Next.js build
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── index.ts            # CLI entry point and orchestrator
│   │   ├── api-clients.ts      # OrgBook / BC Data Catalogue / BC Registries callers
│   │   ├── scraper.ts          # Playwright-based fallback scraper
│   │   └── types.ts            # PermitRequirement, ExtractionResult, ScraperConfig
│   ├── output/                 # JSON output written at runtime
│   ├── package.json            # Separate deps: playwright, tsx, typescript
│   └── tsconfig.json           # Separate TS config — compiled independently
│
├── docs/                       # Reference docs and prompt templates (not deployed)
├── public/                     # Static assets (logo.png)
├── postcss.config.mjs          # PostCSS → @tailwindcss/postcss
├── tsconfig.json               # Root TS config for the Next.js app only
└── package.json                # Root deps for the Next.js app
```

## Where to Put New Code

| What you're adding | Where it goes |
|--------------------|---------------|
| New page / route | `src/app/<route>/page.tsx` |
| New domain entity or React context | `src/entities/<domain>/model/` |
| New self-contained feature component | `src/features/<feature-name>/ui/` |
| Shared TypeScript types | `src/shared/types/` |
| Shared constants or config data | `src/shared/constants/` |
| Reusable UI primitives (button, input) | `src/shared/ui/` (create if needed) |
| Reusable hooks | `src/shared/hooks/` (create if needed) |
| New scraper API client | `scraper/src/api-clients.ts` |
| New scraper types | `scraper/src/types.ts` |
| Static images / fonts | `public/` |

## Conventions

- **Path alias**: use `@/` for all imports inside `src/` (e.g. `@/shared/types/business`).
- **Client components**: add `"use client"` only when the component needs browser APIs or React state. Pages that are purely data-driven (like `roadmap/page.tsx`) stay as Server Components by default.
- **Step data is the single source of truth**: `STEP_CONFIGS` in `src/shared/constants/steps.ts` drives both the roadmap list and each step detail page. Do not hard-code step data in individual pages.
- **IntakeData flows via context**: collect user input through `IntakeProvider` / `useIntake`. Do not pass intake fields as URL params or duplicated local state.
- **Scraper is isolated**: the `scraper/` directory has its own `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, and `node_modules`. Never import from `scraper/` inside `src/`, and never import from `src/` inside `scraper/`.

## Rules

- Do NOT add scraper dependencies (`playwright`, `tsx`) to the root `package.json` unless they are used in the Next.js app itself (they cause the root TypeScript compiler to resolve scraper modules that live outside the app boundary).
- Do NOT create new pages by duplicating layout chrome (header, footer). Layout belongs in `src/app/layout.tsx`.
- Do NOT define `StepConfig` data inline in page files. All step configs live in `src/shared/constants/steps.ts`.
- Do NOT add business logic or data fetching directly inside `src/app/**` pages. Extract it to an entity model or feature slice.
- Do NOT place shared types inside a feature or entity folder. Types needed across multiple layers go in `src/shared/types/`.
- The scraper's `output/` folder is runtime-generated. Do not commit `scraper/output/*.json` or reference its contents from the frontend.
